04/10/2004
ATHENS, Greece -- Justice Minister Anastasios Papaligouras on Sunday (3 October) pledged reforms and improvements that would make the judicial system more efficient and transparent. 
He said the ministry's priority would be to ensure speed and quality in judicial administration, as well as to modernise the correctional system. 
Papaligouras added that a new package of bills, currently being drafted by the government, would seek to ensure the independence of the judiciary and to strengthen the fight against corruption and crime. 
(ANA - 04/10/04)
